{
  "texts": [
    "Each model run was parallelized over 4 AMD Radeon Instinct MI50s with a batch size of 200.",
    "Models were trained for up to 8 epochs where each epoch was saved as a checkpoint with a variety of hyperparameters.",
    "We used a scheduled learning rate that began at 0.001 and had an exponential decay constant of either 0.3 or 0.5 and an adaptive learning rate that would lower the learning rate by 0.25 if the training accuracy did not improve by 0.1% after either 30 K, 50 K, and 60 K training instances.",
    "Weights were updated with the Adam optimizer and all convolutional layers had weight decay regularization of 0.001.",
    "Model benchmarking."
  ]
}